"{\"uid\": \"rappler.com-sports-triathlon-goes-ahead-river-seine-passes-pollution-tests-paris-olympics-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  SUMMARY  This is AI generated summarization, which may have errors.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 69, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19, \"end\": 21, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999504217051695, \"rank\": 4.9578272924266966e-05, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For context, always refer to the full article.\", \"from\": 70, \"to\": 116, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"GOOD ENOUGH.\", \"from\": 118, \"to\": 130, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"General view of the river and the Eiffel Tower as the Men's Individual Triathlon is postponed as pollution levels in the river Seine remain too high.\", \"from\": 131, \"to\": 280, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 202, \"end\": 211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Triathlon\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 3.146165591541252e-13, \"text\": \"Triathlon\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Triathlon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Triathlon\"}, {\"begin\": 258, \"end\": 263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.999999998797648, \"rank\": 1.1663392490218048e-09, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fabrizio Bensch/Reuters  PARIS, France - Organizers cleared the Olympic women's andmen's triathlonsto go ahead on Wednesday, July 31, after the latest Seine river water tests showed lower levels of bacteria, ending days of uncertainty over whether the central Paris swim was viable after heavy rains.\", \"from\": 282, \"to\": 582, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 282, \"end\": 290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fabrizio_Colonna\", \"score\": 0.9880833485679694, \"rank\": 0.01206037062121318, \"text\": \"Fabrizio\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fabrizio_Colonna\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fabrizio_Colonna\"}, {\"begin\": 298, \"end\": 305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 0.9999999946151092, \"rank\": 5.3847013667855e-09, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 314, \"end\": 320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9986312538527506, \"rank\": 0.0008122543835361503, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 433, \"end\": 438, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.999999998797648, \"rank\": 1.1663392490218048e-09, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 542, \"end\": 547, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999974989, \"rank\": 2.6063757218806623e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's triathlon had been scheduled to take place on Tuesday, July 30, but was postponed until Wednesday after the river failed water quality tests.\", \"from\": 584, \"to\": 735, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"News that the races would go ahead on Wednesday came as a relief for teams and athletes, as well as for Paris authorities who have promised residents a swimmable Seine as a long-term legacy of the Games, with the triathlon a very public test.\", \"from\": 737, \"to\": 979, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 841, \"end\": 846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999974989, \"rank\": 2.6063757218806623e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 899, \"end\": 904, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.999999998797648, \"rank\": 1.1663392490218048e-09, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It is with great joy that we received this news,\\\" Benjamin Maze, technical director for France's triathlon federation, told Reuters.\", \"from\": 981, \"to\": 1114, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1032, \"end\": 1040, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Benjamin\", \"score\": 0.6710250595403966, \"rank\": 0.4896166190970183, \"text\": \"Benjamin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4964182\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Benjamin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Benjamin\"}, {\"begin\": 1070, \"end\": 1076, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9986312538527506, \"rank\": 0.0008122543835361503, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1106, \"end\": 1113, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 0.9999999946151092, \"rank\": 5.3847013667855e-09, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Now that we know we will race, we can mentally switch fully into competition mode.\\\"\", \"from\": 1115, \"to\": 1199, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Fifty-five women representing 34 countries will kick off the contest at 8 am, with France's Cassandre Beaugrand and Britain's Beth Potter, two of the top contenders for gold, set to dive into the river side by side.\", \"from\": 1201, \"to\": 1416, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1284, \"end\": 1290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9986312538527506, \"rank\": 0.0008122543835361503, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1317, \"end\": 1324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9965517695682747, \"rank\": 0.003320501216174222, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 1327, \"end\": 1338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beth_Potter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Beth Potter\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beth_Potter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beth_Potter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's event will take place at 10:45 am, immediately after the women's race.\", \"from\": 1418, \"to\": 1498, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The results of the latest water analyses, received at 3:20 am, have been assessed as compliant by World Triathlon allowing for the triathlon competitions to take place,\\\" Paris 2024 and World Triathlon said in a statement.\", \"from\": 1500, \"to\": 1722, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1599, \"end\": 1614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4115938418569243e-14, \"text\": \"World Triathlon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\"}, {\"begin\": 1686, \"end\": 1701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4115938418569243e-14, \"text\": \"World Triathlon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris has spent 1.4 billion euros ($1.52 billion) of public money on wastewater infrastructure to contain sewage and minimize spillage into the river, and Mayor Anne Hidalgo took a dip earlier this month in a bid to convince doubters that the water will not make them ill.\", \"from\": 1724, \"to\": 1996, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1724, \"end\": 1729, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999974989, \"rank\": 2.6063757218806623e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1885, \"end\": 1897, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The decision to postpone the men's race at the last minute on Tuesday had triggered anger among some athletes.\", \"from\": 1998, \"to\": 2108, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If the priority was the health of the athletes this event would have been moved to another location a long time ago,\\\" Belgium's Marten Van Riel wrote on World Triathlon's Instagram page.\", \"from\": 2110, \"to\": 2297, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2229, \"end\": 2236, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9759855385899251, \"rank\": 0.024595827802695643, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 2239, \"end\": 2254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marten_Van_Riel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marten Van Riel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marten_Van_Riel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marten_Van_Riel\"}, {\"begin\": 2264, \"end\": 2279, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4115938418569243e-14, \"text\": \"World Triathlon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are just puppets in a puppet show.\\\"\", \"from\": 2299, \"to\": 2338, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The gamble that the river would be clean enough for the triathlon was never guaranteed to pay off as water quality varies widely day-to-day, with rainfall causing concentrations of infection-causing bacteria like E. coli to rise.\", \"from\": 2340, \"to\": 2569, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Wednesday's races were given the green light despite rain overnight and forecasts for showers around midday which could hit towards the end of the men's event.\", \"from\": 2571, \"to\": 2730, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Organizers make the call based on analysis of river samples taken the previous day at 5 am combined with a discussion between experts on overnight weather, according to Paris 2024.- Rappler.com  How does this make you feel?\", \"from\": 2732, \"to\": 2955, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2901, \"end\": 2911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5207123651308024e-21, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2914, \"end\": 2925, \"title\": \"h